								<div class="title" id="post-title-1358309">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agent-angus-smith" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1275214); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1275214&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183008" alt="Agent Angus Smith" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1275214)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agent-angus-smith" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1275214); return false;" >Agent Angus Smith</a></span> <span class="odate time_1327502049 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">25 Jan 2012 14:34</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1358309">
									

<p>I will remove 'morbidly comical' description, I was going on the tone of several other established SCPs such as the Game show of Death <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-024">024</a>;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&#8230;restricted until researchers can prove in their requisition reports that they need the personnel for actual experiments rather than for personal recreation. I have seen the recordings myself and have to admit that they are amusing on some level,&#8230;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The descriptions can easily be summarized and sanitized, I got the first and last ones from historical sources, which went into a similar level of detail, I agree it is graphic, perhaps more than necessary.</p>
<p>The poltergeist-like entity is the collector and caretaker. The ambiguity is whether it is also the artist and causes or facilitates the incidents.</p>
<p>The actual deaths do not change. The idea is that the mirrors have captured not just the event, but some of their personality or perhaps a scrap of their soul. This creates a certain amount of self-awareness that manifests and is forced to re-experience the event in varied ways. These tortured shards of memories are then put on display for the cruel amusement of the patrons of the gallery. I felt this would be more compelling than a simple recording that could have been made with a video camera.</p>
<p>There are a lot of deaths near a mirror every year. I felt that they had decided that they felt the odds of creating a new mirror for the collection were slim. Perhaps if they brought a new mirror into the containment area and did it there it might be more likely to succeed. Concern over possibly disrupting the entity's routine might be a factor, since the containment seems tenuous. It could be good to mention this in the entry. I like the philosophy that containment is the primary concern, and experimentation is secondary in importance.</p>
<p>I appreciate your feedback and will do some revisions.</p>
<p>[Edit] I am not familiar with Final Destination. Any similarities are coincidental.</p>

